            i
          
        
        
          log
          
            2
          
        
        ⁡
        
          p
          
            i
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathrm {H} (T)=\operatorname {I} _{E}\left(p_{1},p_{2},\ldots ,p_{J}\right)=-\sum _{i=1}^{J}p_{i}\log _{2}p_{i}}
  where 
  
    
      
        
          p
          
            1
          
        
        ,
        
          p
          
            2
          
        
        ,
        …
      
    
    {\displaystyle p_{1},p_{2},\ldots }
   are fractions that add up to 1 and represent the percentage of each class present in the child node that results from a split in the tree.

  
    
      
        =
        −
        
          ∑
          
