    {\displaystyle I_{E}([3,3],[6,2])=I_{E}({\text{windy or not}})={\frac {6}{14}}\cdot 1+{\frac {8}{14}}\cdot 0.81=0.89}
  Now we can calculate the information gain achieved by splitting on the windy feature.

  
    
      
        IG
        ⁡
